"title": "2051: Jesus Christ, majesty of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2051: jesus christ, majesty of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The glorious splendour of Jesus Christ's royal authority belongs to him by right and is reaffirmed through his exaltation to the Father's right hand.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ shared in God's majesty before time began</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:5\">JHN 17:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:24\">JHN 17:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:15\">COL 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:13\">REV 22:13</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ renounced his majesty to become a human being</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:6–2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:2-Isa53:3\">ISA 53:2–53:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:3-John13:5\">JHN 13:3–13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:9\">2CO 8:9</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's majesty seen in his earthly ministry</h2>\n<h3>At the transfiguration</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:16\">2PE 1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:2\">MAT 17:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:2-Mark9:3\">MRK 9:2–9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:29\">LUK 9:29</a></p>\n<h3>At the entry into Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:9-Matt21:10\">MAT 21:9–21:10</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:9-Mark11:10\">MRK 11:9–11:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:37-Luke19:38\">LUK 19:37–19:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:13\">JHN 12:13</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:5\">MAT 21:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:15\">JHN 12:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:9\">ZEC 9:9</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's majesty is reaffirmed through his exaltation</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is exalted to the throne of God's majesty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:31\">ACT 5:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:1\">HEB 8:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:22\">1PE 3:22</a></p>\n<h3>A vision of the glorified Christ in his majesty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:13-Rev1:16\">REV 1:13–1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:6-Rev5:8\">REV 5:6–5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:14\">REV 14:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's is majestic in his absolute pre-eminence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:13-Dan7:14\">DAN 7:13–7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:36\">ACT 2:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:25\">1CO 15:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:10-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:10–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:16\">REV 19:16</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's majesty is shown by his authority as judge of all</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31\">MAT 25:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:31\">ACT 17:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:1\">2TI 4:1</a></p>\n<h2>All humanity will see Jesus Christ's majesty</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:64\">MAT 26:64</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:62\">MRK 14:62</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:30\">MAT 24:30</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:26\">MRK 13:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:27\">LUK 21:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:7-2Thess1:10\">2TH 1:7–1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:7\">REV 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:13\">REV 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:15-Rev6:17\">REV 6:15–6:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:9-Rev7:10\">REV 7:9–7:10</a></p>",
